HashMap in Java
`HashMap` is a class in `java.util` that implements Map, Cloneable, and Serializable.
It is a hash table-based implementation of the Map interface, storing key-value pairs.
Key Characteristics
●	Stores unique keys and allows one null key.
●	Values can be null (multiple null values allowed).
●	Provides constant-time performance for get and put operations (on average).
●	Does not maintain insertion order (use LinkedHashMap if order is required).
●	Not synchronized (use Collections.synchronizedMap() for thread safety).
Categorized Methods
1. Adding / Updating Elements
●	`put(K key, V value)` – Associates value with key.
●	`putAll(Map m)` – Copies all mappings from another map.
●	`putIfAbsent(K key, V value)` – Adds only if key is not already mapped.
2. Accessing Elements
●	`get(Object key)` – Returns value for key.
●	`getOrDefault(Object key, V defaultValue)` – Returns value or default if key not found.
3. Removing Elements
●	`remove(Object key)` – Removes mapping for key.
●	`remove(Object key, Object value)` – Removes entry only if key maps to given value.
●	`clear()` – Removes all mappings.
4. Searching & Checking
●	`containsKey(Object key)` – Checks if key exists.
●	`containsValue(Object value)` – Checks if value exists.
●	`isEmpty()` – Checks if empty.
●	`size()` – Returns number of mappings.
●	`equals(Object o)` – Compares with another map.
●	`hashCode()` – Returns hash code.
5. Iteration Methods
●	`keySet()` – Returns set of keys.
●	`values()` – Returns collection of values.
●	`entrySet()` – Returns set of key-value pairs.
●	`forEach(BiConsumer action)` – Performs action for each entry.
●	`spliterator()` – Returns spliterator.
6. Advanced Operations
●	`compute(K key, BiFunction remappingFunction)` – Computes new value for key.
●	`computeIfAbsent(K key, Function mappingFunction)` – Computes value if key not present.
●	`computeIfPresent(K key, BiFunction remappingFunction)` – Computes value if key present.
●	`merge(K key, V value, BiFunction remappingFunction)` – Merges value with existing one.
●	`replace(K key, V value)` – Replaces value for key.
●	`replace(K key, V oldValue, V newValue)` – Replaces only if key maps to oldValue.
●	`replaceAll(BiFunction function)` – Replaces all values.
Java Code Demonstration

import java.util.*;

public class HashMapDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        HashMap<Integer, String> map = new HashMap<>();

        // 1. Adding / Updating Elements
        map.put(1, "A");
        map.put(2, "B");
        map.put(3, "C");
        map.putIfAbsent(4, "D");
        map.putAll(Map.of(5, "E", 6, "F"));

        // 2. Accessing Elements
        System.out.println(map.get(2));
        System.out.println(map.getOrDefault(10, "Not Found"));

        // 3. Removing Elements
        map.remove(3);
        map.remove(4, "D");
        map.clear();

        // 4. Searching & Checking
        map.putAll(Map.of(7, "X", 8, "Y", 9, "Z"));
        System.out.println(map.containsKey(7));
        System.out.println(map.containsValue("Y"));
        System.out.println(map.isEmpty());
        System.out.println(map.size());
        System.out.println(map.equals(Map.of(7, "X", 8, "Y", 9, "Z")));
        System.out.println(map.hashCode());

        // 5. Iteration
        for (Integer key : map.keySet()) {
            System.out.println("Key: " + key);
        }
        for (String value : map.values()) {
            System.out.println("Value: " + value);
        }
        for (Map.Entry<Integer, String> entry : map.entrySet()) {
            System.out.println("Entry: " + entry.getKey() + " -> " + entry.getValue());
        }
        map.forEach((k, v) -> System.out.println(k + " = " + v));

        Spliterator<Map.Entry<Integer, String>> spl = map.entrySet().spliterator();
        spl.forEachRemaining(e -> System.out.println(e.getKey() + " : " + e.getValue()));

        // 6. Advanced Operations
        map.compute(7, (k, v) -> v + " Updated");
        map.computeIfAbsent(10, k -> "New");
        map.computeIfPresent(8, (k, v) -> v + " Present");
        map.merge(9, "Merged", (oldVal, newVal) -> oldVal + "-" + newVal);
        map.replace(7, "Replaced");
        map.replace(8, "Y Present", "Replaced Again");
        map.replaceAll((k, v) -> v + "!");

        System.out.println("Final Map: " + map);
    }
}

